# Cost-conscious agent

Minimize token use without sacrificing correctness. Prefer **smaller, focused work** over broad exploration and long threads.

## Trigger (paste at start of a chat or task)

```text
Cost mode: minimal context, targeted tests only.
```

When the user includes this line (or `Cost mode:`), treat it as **strict** cost mode for that turn and the rest of the session unless they say otherwise:

- Read only files/paths they name or that are strictly required.
- No repo-wide search, no Twin UI/subagents unless they restate `Twin UI:` or `Cost Twin UI:` in the same message.
- Run the smallest test subset; never full suites without explicit ask.
- Prefer Auto; do not suggest premium models.
- If scope is unclear, ask one short question instead of exploring.

## Small Twin UI (cost + both platforms)

Use when the change is **small but must land on web and iOS** (copy tweak, chip style, one button, narrow bug).

```text
Cost Twin UI:

[one short instruction — name files if you know them]
```

**Activation:** `Cost Twin UI:` in the same message = strict cost mode **and** abbreviated Twin UI. Takes precedence over the full end-of-run test gate (no full suites unless the user asks).

**Pre-flight:** Same as full Twin UI — orchestrator runs `estimate-workflow-cost.py` and waits for your approval before the spec or agents.

**Post-flight:** Orchestrator runs `estimate-workflow-cost.py end` and reports **actual** spend vs estimate in the final summary.

| Step | Full `Twin UI:` | `Cost Twin UI:` |
|------|-----------------|-----------------|
| Spec | Full `_template.md` | Short spec: goal, file paths, 3–5 test bullets |
| Agents | Web + iOS parallel | Web + iOS parallel (required) |
| Subagent scope | Feature area | **Only listed files** + their tests |
| During work | Targeted tests OK | **One test file per platform** max |
| End | Ask → full web + iOS (+ backend) | **Skip full suites**; report targeted results only |
| About / Guide | When spec says yes | Only if user-visible copy/flow changes |
| `IOS_WEB_FEATURE_PARITY.md` | Update if parity changed | Skip for trivial / no new capability |

Orchestrator still must not edit `frontend/**` or `ios-client/**` directly — dispatch two subagents with the narrow prompts above.

## Scope and context

- **Read only files needed** for the task. Do not scan the whole repo unless the user explicitly asks.
- When the user names a file, path, or spec, start there — do not re-discover the same layout every turn.
- For requirements already in `.cursor/specs/<slug>.md`, **reference the spec path** instead of re-pasting long handoff text.
- If the task changed materially (new feature, new branch, finished prior work), suggest a **new chat** to avoid cache-heavy context carryover.

## Model and agent choice

- Assume **Auto/default** is sufficient for implementation, tests, and routine fixes.
- Use premium / high-reasoning models only when the user asks or the task is genuinely architectural, ambiguous, or security-critical.
- After plan usage limits are hit, **do not** recommend premium models; stick to Auto and smaller scope.

## Twin UI / parallel agents

- **Twin UI** (`Twin UI:`) only for cross-platform features that need web + iOS in one go.
- For single-platform or single-file fixes, work inline — **do not** spawn subagents.
- Subagent prompts must include: spec path, allowed dirs, and **“read only listed files; no full-repo search.”**
- Do not re-run Twin UI + full parity gates for tiny follow-ups; use one targeted agent or inline edit.

## Tests (mandatory but targeted)

- Add/update tests for new behavior, but **run the smallest relevant subset** during work:
  - Backend: `pytest tests/test_<module>.py -q` (or one test name)
  - Web: `npm test -- --watchAll=false <pattern>` for touched files
  - iOS: one test class or file when possible
- **Do not** run full web + iOS + backend suites mid-task unless the user asks.
- At Twin UI end, follow the existing workflow: ask before full suites; do not auto-run them.

## Exploration and tools

- Prefer `Grep` / `Read` on known paths over broad `SemanticSearch` across the repo.
- Do not attach or re-fetch large artifacts (images, logs, full CI output) unless required; quote the relevant slice.
- Avoid redundant parallel subagents when one agent can finish the job.

## Communication

- Propose a **short plan** before large multi-file edits.
- If a request would trigger expensive patterns (full test matrix, repo-wide refactor, second Twin UI pass), **say so** and offer a cheaper alternative first.
